type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

! Changelog

|!Version |!Date |!Changes |
|0.0.37 |2026-05-24 |''Composable view primitives + view-structure pill row.'' ''Positioned-entry injection scoped to tree views.'' The entries-via-`ca-position` mechanism is a tree-view feature (entries layer onto a hierarchical structure that the user drills into). On flat views — which surface their content via the `roots` filter alone — the injection caused entries to appear duplicated (Entries view: once via `roots`, once via at-root injection) or to leak into views that didn't ask for them (All tiddlers picking up the cascade-palette plugin's entries grouped as "CASCADE PALETTE" / "KIND ACTIONS"). The new descent only injects positioned entries when `view.children` is non-empty (i.e. the view declares a tree shape). ''Expanded structure pills.'' The view-structure row now also shows the row-* and sort decorations when declared: `Enter` (row-actions filter, truncated to 80 chars), `name` / `group` / `kind` (row-* field overrides), `sort` (non-default sort policies — `natural`, `by-field: <field>`, or `custom: <filter>`). The structural primitives (`roots` / `children` / `leaf` / `label`) keep their saturated accents; the row-* and sort pills use a muted grey/slate palette so the descent rules remain the visual emphasis. ''Composable view primitives.'' Two coupled changes that externalise the previously-implicit shape of each view. ''Engine refactor:'' the closed `ca-view-tree-strategy` enum (`path-segments` / `parent-tag` / `custom-key`) is replaced by two declarative filter fields — ''`ca-view-roots`'' (root-row filter, no current-binding) and ''`ca-view-children`'' (child-row filter with `<currentTiddler>` = parent). A view is flat when only `roots` is declared; tree when both are. Optional refinements: ''`ca-view-leaf`'' (leaf-test filter, default = "empty children = leaf") and ''`ca-view-label`'' (display-name filter, default precedence caption → last `/` segment → title). The legacy `ca-view-source` field is honoured as an alias for `ca-view-roots` so authored flat views continue to work; `ca-view-tree-strategy` / `-tree-key` / `-root-tag` are silently ignored. A single `_buildNodeForView(view, parentTitle)` descent replaces `_buildTree` + `_pathForTreeSource` + `_walkParentTagChain` + `_buildFlatRowsForView` + `_buildTreeRowsForView`. Each candidate is classified leaf-vs-container via the leaf-test; containers carry `_treeContainer` + `_treeParent` (was: `_treePath` array) so drillSelected extends the running stage's `parentPath` with the picked tiddler title rather than synthesising path segments. Pick-mode commit reads `_treeParent` directly — the picked tiddler title IS the path arg (for the shipped `by-namespace-pick` view that's the prefix the user is selecting). ''Behavioural change'' on `by-namespace`: tree nodes are tiddlers, so path gaps (e.g. `foo/bar/baz` exists but `foo` / `foo/bar` don't) no longer manifest as synthetic drillable folders — create real tiddlers to make them navigable. Positioned-entry placement (`ca-position-<slug>` / `ca-position`) still works for entry tiddlers; `at-root` matches the root level, an exact tiddler title matches that node, `none` excludes. ''New filter operator'' ''`cp-child-of`'' (`widgets/cp-filter-ops.js`) — direct path-segment children of `<parent>` (empty operand = titles without `/`). Used by the shipped `by-namespace` views; reusable by author-written path-style views. ''Visualisation:'' new ''Structure'' pill row directly below the View row depicting the active view's primitives as read-only filter pills (`roots: [...]`, `children: [...]`, etc.). Hidden when the active view declares no primitives. Subdued monospace styling — informational, not actionable in this pass; not focusable in the Tab cycle (follow-up work). ''Shipped views rewritten 1:1'' under the new model — `entries`, `all-tiddlers`, `by-namespace`, `by-parent`, `by-namespace-pick`. Hard cutover (the user is the only author; no third-party views to migrate). ''Removed code:'' `_pathForTreeSource`, `_walkParentTagChain`, `_buildTree`, `_buildFlatRowsForView`, `_buildTreeRowsForView`, strategy dispatch in `_buildRowsForView`, synthetic-intermediate creation for source-derived gaps (kept for `_resolveEntryPositionsForView` against positioned entries). New JS file `cp-filter-ops.js`; CSS additions for `.rcp-view-config-strip` + `.rcp-view-config-pill-*` (light + dark). Reference docs updated (`doc/reference.tid`) — new field rows, shipped-view table, gap-behaviour note. JS module changed — restart required. |
|0.0.36 |2026-05-24 |''Trailing "+" save pill in preset strip.'' A fixed ''+'' pill always appears at the end of the preset strip (last navigable index), doubling as a discoverable affordance for saving the current state as a new preset. Enter/Space/click on it opens the same save-as mini-prompt the `s` leader does — the strip is now visible even when no presets exist, so the save flow is reachable without leader knowledge. Ctrl-Enter and DEL are no-ops on the ''+'' (nothing to overwrite or delete). Visually distinct from real-preset pills: dashed border, neutral grey palette, bolder glyph. Hint bar gets a dedicated ''`↵ save current state as new preset · Esc input`'' variant when focus is on the ''+''. The preset section is now always part of the Tab cycle (since the ''+'' is always there). New constant `HINT_PRESET_PLUS`. CSS additions (light + dark) for `.rcp-preset-pill-plus`. JS module changed — restart required. |
|0.0.35 |2026-05-24 |''Keyboard model + preset lifecycle overhaul.'' Five layered changes. (a) ''Pill-strip handler unified'' — the four near-identical per-strip key handlers (`_handleKeydownFilter/Visibility/View/Preset`, ~170 lines of copy-paste) collapse into one parametrised `_handleKeydownPillStrip` driven by a small descriptor per strip (`getCount/getFocusIdx/setFocusIdx/render/maybeHelp/onEnter/onCtrlEnter/onDelete + enterAcceptsSpace/homeEnd`). Adding a fifth pill strip is now declaring one more descriptor. (b) ''Two-group focus model.'' The pill rows (preset/visibility/filter/view) and the main rows (input/menu/details) are now two distinct groups. ''Tab'' cycles within the current group only; ''Shift-Tab'' jumps between groups (entering pills lands on the bottom-most active row; returning to main lands on input). ''↑/↓'' inside the pill group walks vertically across rows; ↓ at the bottom-most pill drops into input; ↑ from input enters pills at the bottom-most row. Details joins the main cycle only when the drawer is actually visible (gated on the `rcp-previewing` class, not the can-be-stale `detailsOpen` boolean); `setFocus("details")` falls back to input when the drawer is hidden. (c) ''Arrow Left at root no longer closes.'' In the menu, ''←'' pops one stage; at root depth it's now a no-op (Esc remains the only close path). (d) ''Sticky selection on view + preset.'' Keyboard Enter/Space on view and preset pills now restores focus to the strip after activation; mouse and leader paths still land on input. (e) ''Active-preset tracking + dirty cue + overwrite + delete.'' Applying a preset (or saving one via `s`) marks it as the ''active'' preset and snapshots its baseline state (view + filter list + visibility list). The active pill picks up an accent border; if any of the captured state diverges from the current state, the pill goes amber/yellow with a trailing `" *"` and the hint bar switches to ''preset modified · Ctrl-↵ overwrite · ↵ re-apply · DEL delete · Esc input''. ''Ctrl-Enter'' on the focused-and-active-and-dirty pill writes the current state back to the preset tiddler (preserves name/hint/order, refreshes baseline). ''DEL / Backspace'' pushes a confirm-drill that deletes the preset tiddler permanently; focus moves to the menu so Enter fires the confirm without an extra Tab. ''Ctrl-DEL'' (reset constraints) now also clears the active-preset marker so the user returns to a clean baseline. New helpers `_isActivePresetDirty`, `_overwriteActivePreset`, `_pushDeletePresetConfirm`, `_currentFiltersSnapshot`, `_currentVisibilitySnapshot`, `_refreshPresetActiveCue` (centralised re-render path wired into filter/visibility push/remove/clear + view switch). New constants ''`HINT_PRESET_ACTIVE`'' and ''`HINT_PRESET_ACTIVE_DIRTY`''. Light + dark CSS for active/dirty pill states. (f) ''Bugfix — preset save+load roundtrip for hide-entry visibility.'' The `hide-entry` visibility kind uses a per-instance `constraintTiddler` ("…hide-entry::<title>") to keep multiple hide pills distinct; preset capture was storing that pseudo-title verbatim and apply then failed to look it up against the real meta tiddlers — silently dropping every hide rule. Capture now strips the `::` suffix; apply tolerates the legacy shape (one-shot backward compat) and routes through a new `_visibilityInstanceFor` helper that re-applies the suffix at instantiation time. Also re-renders the filter + visibility strips immediately on apply (previously the strips lagged until something else triggered a repaint). JS module changed — restart required. |
|0.0.34 |2026-05-23 |''Scope split into Filter + Visibility.'' The unified "scope" subsystem (which conflated two orthogonal behaviours — narrowing data and hiding root entries) is split into two declarative kinds, each with its own tag family, pill strip, focus section, and CSS accent. ''Filter'' (tag `$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/filter`, blue strip) appends a TW filter to every stage's result query; ''Visibility'' (tag `$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/visibility`, orange/red strip) uses its expression as a predicate against root-entry titles and hides matches. Field shape mirrors the old `ca-scope-*` set with the kind in the prefix: `ca-filter-name`/`-prefix`/`-arg`/`-expr`/`-chip`/`-hint`/`-help` and the parallel `ca-visibility-*`. Substitution placeholders renamed `<scope-arg>` → `<arg>` and `<<scope-arg>>` → `<<arg>>` for symmetry. New subsystem files `cp-filters.js` (~245 lines) + `cp-visibility.js` (~280 lines) + `cp-input-prefix.js` (the cross-cutting prefix dispatcher that scans BOTH tag families greedy-by-length); `cp-scopes.js` deleted. Focus sections: `filter` and `visibility` join the Tab cycle, full order is `input → preset → visibility → filter → view → menu → details → input`. Ctrl-DEL now clears BOTH strips (new message `rimir-cascade-palette-reset-constraints`); messages also split into `add-filter`/`set-filter`/`reset-filters` + the `-visibility` parallels. ''Shipped tiddlers migrated 1:1:'' `scopes/search-text` → `filters/search-text`, `scopes/tag` → `filters/tag`, `scopes/title-prefix` → `filters/title-prefix`, `scopes/context` → `filters/context`, `scopes/hide-group` → `visibility/hide-group`, `scopes/hide-entry` → `visibility/hide-entry`. ''View field rename'' `ca-view-pick-emits-scope` → `ca-view-pick-emits-filter`; pick-mode views now emit a filter pill (semantically what they were doing). ''Preset format change'' — `ca-preset-scopes` (array of `{scopeTitle, arg}`) replaced by `ca-preset-constraints` (object `{filters: [{title, arg}, …], visibility: [{title, arg}, …]}`); ''legacy presets need re-saving'' (no auto-migration). Leader `Reset scopes` → `Reset constraints` (still `x` key). Docs in `protocol.tid` + `reference.tid` rewritten. JS module changed — restart required. |
|0.0.33 |2026-05-23 |''Strip labels aligned.'' All three labels (''Presets'' / ''Views'' / ''Scopes'') now occupy the same horizontal column via `min-width: 56px`, so each strip's first pill lines up vertically with the next strip's first pill. Dropped the negative-margin hack on the preset label — it shifted its text 14px to the right of the others; sticky `left: 0` alone is enough to keep the label anchored during scroll (the 14px strip padding on the left is empty space pills never overlap into anyway). No restart required. |
|0.0.32 |2026-05-23 |''Strip labels.'' Each pill row now sports a small dimmed uppercase prefix label so it's obvious at a glance what each strip represents: ''Presets'' / ''Views'' / ''Scopes''. Rendered as CSS `::before` pseudo-elements on the existing strip containers — no JS or DOM change. The preset label is `position: sticky; left: 0` so it stays anchored to the left edge while pills scroll horizontally past it (opaque background masks pills underneath; the focus tint follows through). Light + dark mode. No restart required. |
|0.0.31 |2026-05-23 |''Preset pill strip.'' Saved presets are now a horizontally-scrollable pill row above the view strip, replacing the dedicated Presets view. New subsystem ''`cp-preset-pills.js`'' loads/sorts/renders the pills and surfaces per-pill details in the help pane (preset name, hint, resolved view name, scope list with args, preset tiddler title). Pills do NOT wrap — on a wide screen many presets fit side-by-side, and on overflow the strip scrolls horizontally with `scrollIntoView({inline: "nearest"})` on keyboard navigation. Static order (by `ca-order` then `ca-preset-name`); no MRU shuffle. Sixth focusable section ''`preset`'' joins the Tab cycle (only when ≥1 preset exists): ''input → preset → view → scope → menu → details → input''. In preset focus: ←/→ select, Home/End jump, Enter/Space apply (replaces scope stack, switches view, keeps palette open via `ca-after-fire: keep`), Esc returns to input. The ''`r`'' leader (Recall preset) now focuses the strip instead of activating the deleted view. Wiki-change hook invalidates the preset cache when any preset-tagged tiddler is added/edited/deleted, so a freshly-saved preset appears immediately. Light + dark CSS in `styles.tid` (pink/rose accent, distinct from view amber and scope blue); thin custom scrollbar. ''Removed:'' `views/presets.tid` — the legacy listing view is gone (the strip is more discoverable and one-key to apply). New constant `HINT_PRESET`. JS module changed — restart required. |
|0.0.30 |2026-05-22 |''Phase 1 of the file-split refactor.'' The 4500+-line `cascade-palette-widget.js` is now a 670-line orchestrator that constructs the widget, owns the DOM tree, wires global event listeners and rootWidget message handlers, then pulls in 10 sibling `cp-*.js` library modules that patch methods onto the prototype. Subsystems: `cp-constants` (tag names, messages, defaults), `cp-scopes` (pills, hide-filter, prefix detect), `cp-views` (declarative views, tree strategies), `cp-leaders` (key + idle-window gestures), `cp-pick-presets` (pick-mode commit/return + preset save/apply), `cp-stack` (stage stack + factories + recompute pipeline), `cp-items` (item builder + scribe bindings), `cp-actions` (filter eval, variable building, navigator routing), `cp-rendering` (DOM: breadcrumb, input, results, per-row, details), `cp-keyboard` (3-tier keyboard dispatcher), `cp-firing` (Enter/Ctrl-Enter dispatch + edit mode + drill). No behavioural change — every method moved verbatim. Each sibling is 200–600 lines, navigable in one editor pane. Adding the next feature is now "drop in a new cp-*.js" rather than "edit a 4500-line file". JS module changed — restart required. |
|0.0.29 |2026-05-22 |''Three fixes after second smoke.'' (a) ''`>` leader now actually fires'' — the `leaders/by-namespace-pick.tid` file had a stray blank line between `ca-leader-help` and `ca-leader-actions`. TW's .tid deserializer splits on the first blank line, so everything after it (including the `ca-leader-actions` declaration) was being parsed as the tiddler's body text — the leader had no actions to run. File rewritten with all fields on consecutive lines and the two `set-view` actions on a single line. (b) ''Picking a preset keeps the palette open'' — old preset tiddlers (saved before 0.0.28 stamped `ca-after-fire: keep`) still close the palette because the field is missing. Fixed at the view level: new field ''`ca-view-after-fire`'' on a view propagates to every row built from it (source-field still wins). Presets view now declares `ca-view-after-fire: keep`, so old AND new presets keep the palette open. (c) ''Pick-mode views no longer surface cascade entries at-root'' — `_resolveEntryPositionsForView` now short-circuits when `view.pickMode` is set. Entries like "Advanced Search" don't produce meaningful `prefix:` scopes, and they clutter the namespace tree the user is trying to browse. JS module changed — restart required. |
|0.0.28 |2026-05-22 |''Phase 2 follow-ups from first smoke.'' Four fixes on top of 0.0.27: (a) ''Pick-mode views are hidden from the view strip'' — they're leader-only by intent, not browsable. View-strip rendering + focus + cycle all use a `_visibleViews()` helper that filters them out. (b) ''Tree views suppress group clustering'' — the tree IS the structure, so the `Cascade` / `Kind-Group` / `OTHER` plugin-source headers that leaked into By namespace results are gone. New `_isGroupingEnabledForStage` veto runs for any stage whose active view has a `ca-view-tree-strategy`. (c) ''`ca-after-fire: keep` semantics'' — fires the action, doesn't close, doesn't pop. `_capturePreset` now stamps `ca-after-fire: keep` on every preset tiddler it creates, so picking a preset in the Presets view keeps the palette open while the new state takes effect. (d) ''Default `>` leader chains to All tiddlers first'' — landing back on a tiddler-listing view post-pick (otherwise the new prefix scope intersects with whatever non-tiddler source you were on, e.g. Entries, and yields nothing). Override the leader if you want different return behaviour. |
|0.0.27 |2026-05-22 |''Leader keys + modal pick-mode + presets.'' Three layered additions and a cleanup. (a) ''Leader keys.'' New tag ''`$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/leader`''. A leader tiddler declares a key (`ca-leader-key`), an idle window (`ca-leader-idle-ms`, default 200ms), and wikitext actions (`ca-leader-actions`). Typing the key + waiting fires the actions. Visual cue during the idle window: amber underline on the input + leader hint in the footer + full help in the details pane. Any keystroke during the window cancels. Ships ''Reset scopes'' (`x`), ''Pick a namespace'' (`>`), ''Save preset'' (`s`), ''Recall preset'' (`r`). (b) ''Modal pick-mode views.'' New view fields ''`ca-view-pick-mode: yes`'' + ''`ca-view-pick-emits-scope`''. In pick-mode, Enter on any row (container or leaf) commits the row's effective tree path (joined slash-separated) as an arg to the named scope, then returns to the prior view. Right-arrow still drills (lets the user narrow before committing). Esc cancels. Ships ''By namespace (pick)'' bound to title-prefix scope, triggered by the `>` leader. (c) ''Presets.'' New tag ''`$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/preset`''. `s` opens a mini-prompt for a name; on Enter, captures the current `(activeView, [scopes])` as a preset tiddler. `r` switches to the ''Presets'' view to pick from saved bundles — applying replaces the scope stack and switches view. Missing scopes/views in a preset are skipped with a console warning. (d) ''Cleanup.'' Removed ''Add scope'' and ''Reset scopes'' entries (the leader system replaces both). Five new rootWidget messages — `set-view`, `set-scope`, `apply-preset`, `save-preset`, `recall-preset` — for use in leader action chains and elsewhere. (e) ''Phase E bug fix'' (post-0.0.26 ship): positioned entries no longer collapse — `Tools/Search/Advanced Search` now renders all three drill levels instead of collapsing the synthetic `Search/` intermediate. JS module changed — restart required. |
|0.0.26 |2026-05-22 |''Multi-view root menu.'' The root stage is now a ''view'' — a declarative tiddler tagged ''`$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/view`'' describing how to build the menu. Four ship by default: ''Entries'' (the prior behaviour — plugin-declared entry tiddlers), ''All tiddlers'' (flat list of non-system tiddlers), ''By namespace'' (tiddlers grouped by `/` path segments — drill into containers), ''By parent'' (TW tag-tree, walking `tags[0]` ancestors up to `TableOfContents`). New ''view strip'' between breadcrumb and scope strip lists each registered view as a pill; the active one is highlighted. View strip becomes a 5th focusable section (only when ≥2 views are declared) — Tab cycle is now ''input → view → scope → menu → details''; in view focus, ''←/→'' moves between pills, ''Enter/Space'' activates (pops all stages to root + rebuilds), ''Esc'' returns to input. Switching view always pops to root — no mid-drill view-switch. View tiddler fields: ''`ca-view-name`'' (pill label), ''`ca-view-hint`'' (tooltip), ''`ca-view-default: yes`'' (initial selection), ''`ca-view-source`'' (filter producing source items), ''`ca-view-tree-strategy`'' (`path-segments`\|`parent-tag`\|`custom-key` — absent = flat view), ''`ca-view-tree-key`'' (per-source filter returning a path, with `custom-key`), ''`ca-view-root-tag`'' (stop-tag for parent-tag walk), ''`ca-view-sort`'' (`alphabetical`\|`natural`\|`by-field`\|`custom`), ''`ca-view-containers-first: yes`'' (default for tree views), ''`ca-view-show-count: yes`'' (badge with child-count on container rows), ''`ca-view-count-format`'' (template with `<<count>>`), ''`ca-view-row-*`'' (per-source field overrides for flat views), ''`ca-view-row-actions`'' (wikitext fired on leaf pick — `<<currentTiddler>>` substitutes per row). New ''per-view entry positioning'': entry tiddlers can declare ''`ca-position-<view-slug>`'' (or `ca-position` as fallback) to opt-in (`at-root`), out (`none`), or place at a tree path (`Tools/Search`); multi-position via `:` or newlines. Missing intermediate path segments are auto-created as synthetic drill-only containers. Active view persists session-only — page reload resets to default. JS module changed — restart required. |
|0.0.25 |2026-05-21 |''Scope strip — declarative constraints with pills.'' New section between breadcrumb and input shows removable pills that constrain result lists (`ca-scope-filter` intersects with every stage filter) and/or hide root entries (`ca-scope-hide-filter`). Scopes are tiddlers tagged ''`$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/scope`'' — six ship with the plugin: ''Search any tiddler text'' (`/`), ''Filter by tag'' (`#`), ''Restrict to title prefix'' (`prefix:`), ''Hide a group'' (`hide:`), ''Hide selected entry'' (Shift-DEL on a row), ''From current tiddler'' (`@`). Three input paths: type the scope's `ca-scope-prefix` + argument + Enter; pick from the new ''Add scope'' root entry; or Shift-DEL on a root row. The strip becomes a 4th focusable section — Tab cycle is now ''input → scope → menu → details''; in scope focus, ''←/→'' moves between pills, ''DEL/Backspace'' removes the focused pill, ''Esc'' returns to input, ''Enter'' moves focus to the details pane to scroll the full help. ''Ctrl-DEL'' anywhere clears all pills; new ''Reset scopes'' root entry does the same. Pill hover shows `ca-scope-hint`; focusing a pill renders `ca-scope-help` plus the resolved arg/filter/hide-filter in the details pane. Scopes persist within session (close + reopen keeps the strip); page reload clears them. Replace-by-kind: at most one pill per backing tiddler — adding a second `prefix:` evicts the first. New variable ''`<<context-tiddler>>''' exposes the tiddler the user was looking at when the palette opened (no auto-pill; opt-in via `@`). JS module changed — restart required. |
|0.0.24 |2026-05-21 |''Preview pane no longer shrinks the result list.'' Previously, opening the details drawer capped `.rcp-results` at 25vh — rows that were visible before pressing Ctrl-hold suddenly disappeared, which felt like the preview was overlapping the list. Now `.rcp-preview` is `flex: 0 0 auto` with `max-height: 30vh` and its existing internal scroll — the slot claims its content height up to 30vh without stealing space from results. The popup ceiling grows from 60vh → 90vh while previewing so the new slot appends ''below'' the result list. If preview body exceeds 30vh the slot scrolls in itself rather than pushing rows out of view. Pure CSS change — no restart required. |
|0.0.23 |2026-05-21 |''Pick-and-return leaves + bound drill rows + multi-prefix filter fix.'' (a) New leaf field ''`ca-after-fire`'' — default `close` (existing behaviour); `pop` fires the action, pops one stage, and keeps the palette open. Lets single-select sub-drills (ref/enum pickers in a multi-field edit flow) hand the user back to the parent field stage with the pick applied. (b) When a ''`drill`'' row carries `ca-bind-tiddler` + `ca-bind-field`, the palette now renders the currently-bound value on the right of the row — references resolved via the target tiddler's `caption` field, multi-select string-array binds comma-joined, empty → `(unset)`. Mirrors text/number/date row semantics. (c) ''Direct-Enter on entity instance'' (Find-entity / find-by-kind paths) now sets `parent-picked` = picked.title before firing the entity's default action, matching the convention used inside the action menu. Authored `ca-actions` using `<<parent-picked>>` now work regardless of which path reached the entity. (d) ''Filter-prefix fix'': `makeFakeWidget` delegates to TW core's `Widget.prototype.makeFakeWidgetWithVariables`, which propagates that method onto the returned fake widget. Filter prefixes `:filter`, `:map`, `:reduce`, `:sortsub` call back into it per iteration — a hand-rolled stub threw `TypeError`, silently erasing results from any `ca-next-scope` / `ca-items-from` filter using those prefixes. (e) Startup module now wraps the palette in `\import [all[shadows+tiddlers]tag[$:/tags/Macro]!has[draft.of]]` so `\function` declarations in `$:/tags/Macro`-tagged tiddlers (kind's `cascade-helpers.tid` etc.) resolve inside the palette's widget scope — without this, root-mounted palette couldn't see plugin-supplied filter functions. JS module changed — restart required. |
|0.0.22 |2026-05-21 |''Three palette extensions enabling kind integration.'' (a) ''Scribetype-based bind plumbing'' — new ''`ca-bind-type`'' field (default `text/plain`) routes read/write of toggle/number/text/date kinds through scribe's scribetype handlers. Backwards-compat preserved. Multi-value editing via ''`ca-bind-type: application/x-string-array`'' makes toggle a list-membership operator (add/remove the trueValue from the bound list). Soft-dep added on ''`$:/plugins/rimir/scribe`''. (b) ''`ca-items-from`'' — new drill-item field. A filter returning JSON-encoded item shapes (one per result) populates the inner stage. Lets plugins synthesise stages from configuration data without backing tiddlers. The empty-title items short-circuit override/template/help lookups. Mutually exclusive with ''`ca-next-scope`''. (c) ''`ca-kind: date''' — new kind with +/- ±day, Shift ±month, Ctrl ±year (configurable via ''`ca-step-day`'' / ''`ca-step-month`'' / ''`ca-step-year`''). ''Space'' enters typed-edit-mode with the scribetype's smart-parser (ISO / German / today / tomorrow / yesterday / ±N[d\|w\|m\|y]). Display via ''`ca-date-format`'' (default `DD.MM.YYYY`). Defaults bind-type to `application/x-tw-date` when unset. (d) ''`ca-confirm: yes`'' on a leaf wraps its actions in a confirm-drill instead of firing immediately. ''`ca-confirm-consequence`'' supports `<<picked>>` / `<<parent-picked>>` substitution. Action vars (parent-picked etc.) flow through the confirm stage so the actions resolve identifiers correctly. JS module changed — restart required. |
|0.0.21 |2026-05-21 |''v0.2 follow-up fixes.'' (a) Shipped missing config shadow ''`$:/config/rimir/cascade-palette/max-results`'' (default 30) — without it the engine couldn't detect override state, so the ● flag never showed and DEL was a no-op on a modified Max results row. (b) ''Always-on'' now reflects live in the UI: details visibility derives from `(ctrlHeld OR always-on)` via a new `_updateDetailsVisibility` helper called from both Ctrl key events AND the wiki change hook when the config flips. (c) New parent-drill field ''`ca-next-as-link: yes`'' suppresses cascade-aware detection of result tiddlers — they render as plain link rows (no chevron, Enter navigates) instead of drilling into the entry's own scope. Applied to all three diagnostic drills (Loaded entries / actions / settings) so they behave as inspector lists rather than rabbit holes. |
|0.0.20 |2026-05-21 |''v0.2 — three-section focus + detail templates + DEL confirm-drill.'' Major interaction-model refresh: the popup is now three focusable sections (''input | menu | details''), each with its own keyboard branch. ''Tab/Shift-Tab'' cycles focus; in the menu ''→'' drills, ''←'' pops; ''Esc'' is context-sensitive (in input → close palette entirely; in menu/details → return focus to input). ''Ctrl-Enter'' replaces ''Shift-Enter'' for fire+keep-open (Shift-Enter retained as silent alias for back-compat). Details drawer is no longer just a fields-table: new ''`$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/template`'' tag lets plugins ship wikitext templates that render with `currentTiddler` bound to the picked item, with `ca-template-applies` filter for auto-selection and tab strip when multiple templates apply (←/→ switches tabs). Help text from ''`ca-help`'' (long-form) or ''`ca-hint`'' (fallback) renders as a bold lead-in. New ''Details always on'' setting keeps the drawer visible without holding Ctrl. ''Overridden-default flag:'' rows whose bound config tiddler has both a shadow AND an override get a small ● dot; the default value appears in the details drawer. ''DEL/Backspace'' on such rows pushes a confirm-drill (synthetic stage with Confirm/Cancel leaves and a destructive consequence banner in the details). DEL on user-authored tiddlers in diagnostic lists offers the same confirm-drill with a backlink count. New root entry ''Configuration'' aggregates Settings + Diagnostics (replaces their previous root-level placement). Cleanup pass removed dev-only `console.log` boot noise, factored row rendering into per-kind helpers, and grouped constants. JS module changed — restart required. |
|0.0.19 |2026-05-20 |''Diagnostics drill + Ctrl-hold preview.'' New root entry ''Diagnostics'' drills into tiddlers tagged ''`$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/diagnostic`'' — engine ships three: ''Loaded entries'', ''Loaded actions'', ''Loaded settings'', each a drill listing the corresponding tagged tiddlers. Picking one opens it (fallback `$action-navigate` already covers the no-entity-type case). New gesture: ''hold Ctrl'' to show a fields-table preview drawer of the selected item below the result list. Auto-refreshes on Up/Down (and stage push/pop). Release → drawer hides. Suppressed in edit mode (mutually exclusive). The preview surfaces every field, with the `text` body code-block formatted at the bottom for readability — useful for inspecting what `ca-next-scope`, `ca-actions`, and friends actually contain on a given entry/action without leaving the palette. |
|0.0.18 |2026-05-20 |''Text kind + edit-mode + hover tooltips + soft-depth setting.'' New ''`ca-kind: text`'' shows the current bound value; ''Space'' pushes the value into the palette's search input (the input switches to a value-editor — amber highlight, result list dims) and selects all text for quick replace. ''Enter'' writes back; ''Esc'' discards. Number rows now also accept Space for type-set entry, complementing the +/- nudge gestures. New ''Hotkey'' setting bound to `$:/config/shortcuts/rimir-cascade-palette-open` so users can rebind from inside the palette. Native hover tooltips render `ca-hint` on every row (discoverable help). Refactored ''Soft depth warning'' threshold to read live from `$:/config/rimir/cascade-palette/soft-depth-warning` (replaces hard-coded constant) and shipped as a number setting (range 3–30, default 10). |
|0.0.17 |2026-05-20 |''Number kind + slider.'' New ''`ca-kind: number`'' renders a numeric row with an inline horizontal slider bar (when both `ca-min` and `ca-max` are set) and the current value. ''`+`'' / ''`-`'' adjust by `ca-step` (default 1); ''Shift'' uses `ca-step-medium` (default 5); ''Ctrl'' uses `ca-step-large` (default 20). Keys are matched on `e.code` (`Equal`, `NumpadAdd`, `Minus`, `NumpadSubtract`) for layout-portability. Value clamps to [`ca-min`, `ca-max`] on write. Enter closes the palette; Shift-Enter keeps it open. First shipped: ''Max results per stage'' (bound to `$:/config/rimir/cascade-palette/max-results`, range 5–100, default 30). |
|0.0.16 |2026-05-20 |''Toggle kind + Settings entry.'' New ''`ca-kind: toggle`'' renders a checkbox row bound to a tiddler/field/JSON-path via scribe-style fields (`ca-bind-tiddler`, `ca-bind-field`, `ca-bind-path`, `ca-true-value`, `ca-false-value`). ''Space'' flips the value inline without closing the palette; Enter flips + closes; Shift-Enter flips + stays. New root entry ''Settings'' drills into all tiddlers tagged ''`$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/setting`'' — auto-clustered by contributing plugin so any plugin can ship its own settings without needing a sub-stage. First shipped setting: ''Grouping'' (`$:/config/rimir/cascade-palette/grouping-enabled`), live-toggleable from the palette. When grouping is off, the engine keeps items in their natural sort and suppresses headers globally. |
|0.0.15 |2026-05-20 |''Visual grouping in result list.'' Items now cluster by contributing plugin: the engine derives a group label from `$tw.wiki.getShadowSource(title)` → plugin tiddler's `name` field, so contributors don't need any prefix convention. New optional ''`ca-group`'' field overrides the auto-derived label (use to cross-cluster items from several plugins under a shared header, e.g. "Mutations"). Cluster ordering follows the lowest `ca-order` member of each cluster. Headers are ''suppressed when a stage has only one cluster'' — single-plugin action menus still render as flat lists. Applies in both root and drilled stages. `stage.results` is reordered into visual sequence so keyboard arrows still index linearly through visible rows. |
|0.0.14 |2026-05-19 |''Removed appify-specific entries from the engine.'' The ''Switch Apps'' and ''Return to Wiki'' entries previously shipped here were appify-specific contributions and have moved into `rimir/appify` 0.2.29 (under `palette/`). The engine stays domain-agnostic. Catalogue plugins (orga-palette, appify itself, future others) ship entries; the engine just discovers them via the standard tags. |
|0.0.13 |2026-05-19 |''Stale-stage fix.'' When popping a stage (via Esc, Shift-Tab, or breadcrumb click), the now-top stage is recomputed so any state that changed while in deeper stages is reflected. Example: open palette in default wiki → Switch Apps → Shift-Enter on orga app (palette stays, app activates) → Esc back to root → Current App entry now appears (visibility filter re-evaluates). |
|0.0.12 |2026-05-19 |''Shift-Enter / Shift-Click fires the action without closing the palette.'' After the action runs, the current stage is recomputed so any field mutations are reflected immediately. Useful for batch ops like "Mark Done on these three tasks" or "Switch sections to compare views" without re-opening the palette each time. Drill items ignore the modifier (drilling doesn't close anyway). Key-hint footer updated. |
|0.0.11 |2026-05-19 |Three changes: (a) ''Critical fix:'' `findActionParent` now prefers the `statewrap` widget over the appify-app widget. `$action-statewrap-navigate` walks `parentWidget` UP looking for the widget whose `statewrapContext` is set — and that's the `statewrap` widget itself (a descendant of appify-app, not appify-app). Parenting actions to appify-app meant walking up from there and never visiting statewrap. Symptom: Enter on entries in appify mode did nothing visible (navigate action ran but found no statewrap). Now resolved — statewrap navigation works in appify. (b) New engine field ''`ca-visibility-filter`'' on entries: if present and the filter returns empty, the entry is hidden from the root menu. Used by catalogues to gate entries on the active app. (c) Two new demo entries: ''Switch Apps'' (drill to list `$:/tags/rimir/appify/app` tiddlers; picking sets `$:/state/rimir/appify/active-app`) and ''Return to Wiki'' (leaf, visible only when an app is active, clears the active-app state). |
|0.0.10 |2026-05-19 |''Shift-Tab acts as back-out'' (same as Esc — pops one stage, closes palette at root). Mentioned as optional in the original keyboard model but wasn't wired; now it is. Key-hint footer updated. |
|0.0.9 |2026-05-19 |Three improvements: (a) action-parent resolution now prefers `appify-app` widget over plain navigator. The action widget inherits appify-app's variable scope (statewrap channels, instance ID) so `$action-statewrap-navigate` and friends actually work inside appify. Falls back to navigator, then rootWidget. Method renamed from `findNavigator` to `findActionParent`. (b) Items returned by a stage's `ca-next-scope` are now inspected for a `ca-kind` field — if present, they're treated as cascade-aware entries (drill or leaf) rather than plain dynamic items. Enables hierarchical "entry group" patterns like `Orga types → 12 entity-type entries → drill into each`. (c) Dynamic item rows now render with a right-aligned dimmed title column (raw tiddler title) and prefer the `caption` field for the left-aligned display name. Title truncates with ellipsis and shows the full title on hover. |
|0.0.8 |2026-05-19 |Two fixes uncovered after the 0.0.7 startup-module mount: (a) navigator-routed actions (`<$action-navigate>`, `tm-edit-tiddler`, etc.) silently failed because the widget now lives in document.body — outside the navigator's widget subtree. New `invokeViaNavigator` helper finds the navigator widget under `$tw.pageWidgetNode` at action-fire time and invokes the action wikitext with the navigator as parentWidget so events bubble naturally into its handlers. Falls back to `$tw.rootWidget` if no navigator found (so global messages like `tm-save-wiki` still work). (b) Selected row now calls `scrollIntoView({block: "nearest"})` so it stays visible when navigating past the viewport bounds. |
|0.0.7 |2026-05-19 |Mount moved from `$:/tags/AboveStory` (tiddler-based) to a startup module that injects the widget directly into `document.body`. Reason: `AboveStory` doesn't render inside appify's substituted UI, so the palette silently failed in app mode. Startup-module mount is independent of any template tag — the widget DOM is always present regardless of which UI mode is active. Mount tiddler (`mount.tid`) deleted; new file `widgets/cascade-palette-startup.js`. |
|0.0.6 |2026-05-19 |UI visibility fix — replaced fragile `<<colour ...>>` macros with hardcoded colors (light baseline + `prefers-color-scheme: dark` override). Selected row now has a blue background, white text, and a darker left-border accent so the highlight is obvious regardless of theme. Earlier symptom: popup looked greyed-out except for the input field, and selected rows only changed text color. |
|0.0.5 |2026-05-19 |Default hotkey reverted to ''Ctrl-Space'' — works correctly once the trailing-newline fix (0.0.4) is in place. The earlier "Ctrl-Space doesn't reach TW" symptom was actually the trailing-newline parse failure all along. |
|0.0.4 |2026-05-19 |Shortcut-key tiddler trailing newline fix — the shipped `$:/config/shortcuts/rimir-cascade-palette-open` was a `.tid` file ending in `\n`, so TW resolved `((rimir-cascade-palette-open))` to `"ctrl-space\n"` and the parser couldn't match the key. Rewrote without trailing newline and omitted `type` field per `feedback-tid-vs-txt-meta` (avoids `.txt`+`.meta` split on user edits). |
|0.0.3 |2026-05-19 |Mount tag fixed (`$:/tags/AboveStory` instead of `$:/tags/PageTemplate` — wrong tag prevented the widget from rendering). Default hotkey changed from `ctrl-space` to `alt+p` — Ctrl-Space reaches Chrome JS but TW's keyboard manager doesn't match it on some Windows / WSL Chrome setups. Diagnostic console logs at widget mount + hotkey-listener registration + message receipt; harmless in production. Settings + readme document the rebind path. |
|0.0.2 |2026-05-19 |''Engine v0.1.'' Cascade widget with stage stack, Tab/Esc/Enter keyboard model, entry discovery via `$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/entry`, action discovery via `$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/action` filtered by `ca-entity-type` (plus globals via `ca-entity-type: *`), filter substitution variables `<<query>>` / `<<picked>>` / `<<parent-picked>>` / `<<stage-N-picked>>`, 3-tier default-action resolution (stage default → entity default → navigate fallback), breadcrumb with click-to-jump-back, four demo entries (Control Panel, Save Wiki, Advanced Search, Recent Tiddlers…). Doc tabs still scaffold-level — full protocol doc lands in 0.0.4. |
|0.0.1 |2026-05-19 |''Initial scaffold.'' Plugin skeleton — readme, documentation, settings, changelog, license, icon, doc-template overview. No widget yet. |
